    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/130">Heinricus</persName> servus servorum Christi et
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus secundum
                        voluntatem dei salvatoris nostrique liberatoris. Quicquid confirmacionis et
                        proprietatis ad eclesiarum dei sanctorumque suorum exaltatione prebuerimus,
                        id nobis ad aeterne beatitudinis bravium et secularis vite profectum esse
                        profuturum verissime credimus. Igitur omnium sancte dei ecclesie fidelium
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum agnoscat universitas, qualiter
                        nos pro dei omnipotentis amore et pro anima amite nostre <persName
                            key="#Offersio/donatio #Queen" ref="#people/1301">Adheleidis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> auguste et ob remedium anime nostrae
                        parentumque nostrorum, rogante domno <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbate</rs>, suo <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobio</rs> ad honore
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3619"
                            key="#Offersio/donatio #Fiscal_property">sancti Salvatoris</orgName>
                        haud procul a menibus <placeName ref="#places/65">Ticinensis</placeName>
                        urbis fundato per hoc nostrum imperiale preceptum, prout iuste et legaliter
                        valemus, confirmamus, quemadmodum ad antecessores meos praeceptali
                        auctoritate confirmata sunt, omnia, que eiusdem venerabili loco donata collata et oblata sunt tam de
                        <rs
                            key="#Offersio/donatio">largifluo dono</rs> memorate amite nostre quam etiam aliqua inscriptione cartarum
                        aliorum hominum, cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellis</rs> <rs
                                key="#Curtes">cortibus</rs> <rs
                                    key="#Royal_slave">servis</rs> <rs
                                        key="#Royal_slave">ancillis</rs> <rs
                                            key="#Royal_aldius">aldianibus</rs> et
                        <rs
                            key="#Royal_aldius">aldianis</rs> <rs
                                key="#Churches">capellis</rs> <rs
                                    key="#Churches">oratoriis</rs> <rs
                                        key="#Villas">villis</rs> <rs
                                            key="#Mansi">mansis</rs> <rs
                                                key="#Landed_possessions">campis</rs> <rs
                                                    key="#Wine">vineis</rs> <rs
                                                        key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs> <rs
                                                            key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs
                            key="#Forests">silvis</rs> <rs
                                key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planiciebus <rs
                                    key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscacionibus</rs> <rs
                                key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> terris cultis et incultis <rs
                                    key="#Tolls #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis</rs> <rs
                                        key="#Ports">portibus</rs>, verum
                        etiam cum omnibus, de quibus venerabili coenobium iuste investituram habet
                        vel habuit ex ea die, qua prefata serenissima amita nostra <rs
                            key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ibi
                        constituit. Confirmamus quidem et firmissimam traditione largimur eidem
                        monaster[i]o domini Salvatoris <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> <orgName key="#Fiscal_property
                                #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries">sancti Anastasii</orgName> una cum 
                        <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Curtes 
                            #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/342">
                            <geogName
                                key="#Curtes 
                                #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/134">Olonna</geogName></placeName>, 
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montecelli</placeName>, <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Erbaria</placeName>, <placeName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >B[asilig]utiam</placeName>, <placeName
                                        key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                        >Frisinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                            >Pastorianum</placeName>,
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Riuoceruinum</placeName>, <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Tullianum</placeName>, <placeName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >Puizolum</placeName>, <placeName
                                        key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                        >Centascum</placeName>, <placeName
                                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                            >Noue</placeName>, <placeName
                                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                                >Urba</placeName>, <placeName
                                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                                    ref="#places/18">Marinco</placeName>, <placeName
                                                        key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                                        >Corianum</placeName>
                        cum omnibus pertinentiis suis, <rs key="#Castle">castellum</rs> da <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Bosco</placeName>, <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Felegariolo</placeName>, terram de
                        <persName key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"><name ref="Petrus Albesanus">
                                Petro Albesano</name></persName>, terram quam tenuit <persName key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"><name ref="Liudualdus">Liutaldus</name></persName> cum 
                        <rs key="#Mansi">manso</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">Pelenzona</geogName></placeName>,
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Armentaria</placeName>, <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                >Blundi</placeName>, <placeName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                    >Gagio</placeName>, <placeName
                                        key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                        >Lagusianum</placeName>, <placeName
                                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                            >Cassina</placeName>, <placeName
                                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                                >Cuguzuda</placeName>, <placeName
                                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                                                    >Garlascum</placeName> cum
                        <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit"
                            >districtum</rs> in circuitu duo miliarium una cum <rs key="#Forests">silva</rs> de 
                        <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Carbonaria</placeName>, de quantum
                        ian dictum monasterium per praeceptum tenere videtur, Uirgemini,
                        Caucon[a]te, viridiarium prope Palatinam portam et sancti Iohannis scitum
                        cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis tam infra civitatem Ticinensem
                        quam extra, Garfiniana, Uicolongo, Bissione, cellam sancti Nazarii,
                        Mauratica, Melaria. Insuper monasterium sancte dei genitricis Marie+ in loco
                        Pomposa constructum, cum quibus ad eum pernere videtur, vel etiam omnes
                        salinas, qua in Comaclo ab supra scripto monasterio domini Salvatoris
                        pertinere decernitur seu in aliis omnibus locis, que+ ian dicto coenobio
                        sancti Salvatoris pertinere cernuntur, illo in proprium corroboramus.
                        Precipientes itaque iubemus, ut nullus episcopus dux marchio comes vicecomes
                        castaldius nullaque imperii nostri magna parvaque persona de rebus mobilibus
                        sive immobilibus sive de qualibet terra disvestere [i]dem monasterium sine
                        legali iudicio presumat. Sancimus insuper et hac nostra imperiali
                        aucto[ri]tate concedimus, ut, si contigerit, quod sepe accidit, quatinus
                        abbas prenominati monasterii huius lucis habitaculum deserat, liceat
                        monachos ex sinu eiusdem e+cclesie+ q[uem meli]orem viderint eligere in
                        patrem, omnium episcoporum vel omnium mor[talium contradi]ccione remota, nec
                        fas sit alicui monacho ex alio monasterio ad id transitum facere sine
                        voluntate monachorum inibi deo servientium in perpetuum. Si quis autem huius
                        nostrae promulgate+ auctoritatis et preceptis violator extiterit sive
                        praedicte+ e+cclesie+ sancti Salvatoris minorationem facere aut in castellis
                        villis vel aliquibuslibet locis eius aribergare, placitum sine eiusdem
                        coenobii abbatis iussione ullatenus tenere aut aliquam angariam vel publicam
                        functionem aut theloneum extorquere vel tollere aut monachos de aliqua re
                        presumpserit molestare, sciat se compositurum auri cocti libras mille,
                        medietatem camere nostre+ ac medietatem abbati eiusdem monasterii qui pro
                        tempore fuerit, et insuper, quod ei deterius est, cum Iuda traditore domini
                        salvatoris nostri, in cuius nomine ian dictum monasterium constructum est,
                        aeternis deputetur incendiis. Ut autem verius credatur hoc preceptum nostra
                        auctoritate peractum, presentem paginam manu propria, ut videtur infra,
                        corroborante sigillo nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni Heinrici (M.)
                        invictissimi imperatoris augusti. Heinricus cancellarius vice Euerardi
                        episcopi et archicancellarii recognovit. (SI. D.) </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
